>Inspecting your equipment = looking at what you are wearing.<br><br>My argument stands, and it holds water quite well, actually. &nbsp;I have a large bladder. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulamil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lamil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 8:40:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Hopefully I can slip this one under the radar.<br><br><br>Sejal, you're a ridiculous @#%$ moron. As a matter of fact, you're the worst kind of moron. I don't know what aggravates me more - your idiotic retorts, or your bizarre aversion to inspections - which borders on mental illness. Jesus Christ you @#%$ wacko, get over yourself and stop crying like a stupid little bitch about something so incredibly minor.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usejaltraurig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sejal Traurig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 8:47:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Celdor, since you seem to have the level of sophistication explained to you, I'll try.. I responded to someone saying &quot;Get over it&quot;. That might be RUDE (And I don't think that anyone would argue very hard otherwise), but it is NOT a flame. <br><br>Now.. What YOU said was that you made a comment at a level too sophisticated for me to grasp. THAT, my 'friend', IS a flame, and is the sort of thing my original posting of '/ignore flame' is intended to address.<br><br>I respond to you now for clarification purposes and not with any intent to ENTER a flame war with you. I hope now, though, that you can understand the differences and subtlties involved, and can contribute something at least moderately relevant to the conversations at hand.<br><br>Ice Weasel, we still disagree.. LOOKING is standing there seeing &quot;He is wearing plate and carrying a sword.&quot; INSPECTING is seeing &quot;This is Mithril plate, those are Velium Fire Wedding Rings, oh look.. an FBSS&quot; And it doesn't take a genious to then look up (Or already KNOW) what the stats of those items are..<br><br>And you STILL are ignoring something ELSE I said in my first post. ASK PERMISSION FIRST and there is no problem. Courtesy is what we are talking about here, and many people's appaernt lake thereof. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uceldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celdor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1962<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 8:55:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Ah, semantics. So, to be a flame in your eyes, one must insult you. If one tells you to get over it and STFU, that is not a flame. Now it begins to make sense.<br><br>Well, not really. <p><br><br><center><br><a href=http://www.stomptokyo.com/movies/wicker-man.html><small><b>I am looking for Rowan Morrison.</b></small></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrechdashadowknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trech Da ShadowKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 657<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 9:01:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> . </span><hr size=1> Sejal or whatever your name is,<br><br>I understand. I too wear Izod clothes. I understand what a pain it truly is to be walking down the street only have every person in a 50ft radius come stare inches above my nipple to see my little izod aligator.<br><br>Seriously though, let me put you to the task. Tell me why its rude when you see a simple line of text that says someone is inspecting you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usejaltraurig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sejal Traurig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 9:04:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Is there anything OTHER than semantics when people are communicating via a written medium? I'd be curious what your definition of a flame is. Any response at all? One in disagreement with you? An aggressive opposition? Insulting another? In some ways any or all of these are flames. I'm not unwilling, however, to talk about things with someone that disagrees with me. Unless of course said person is going to just sit around tossing insults my way. I have better things to do with my day. If someone wants to have a reasoned conversation, so be it. I have nothing against that at all. Yes, he did say STFU.. That part I ignored.. <br><br>Yes, we are talking about semantics.. We are also talking about courtesy.. Additionally we are talking about respect.. The same respect you show someone at Pizza Hut, or the Post Office, or where ever you run into them on the street.. No, I'm not so wrapped up in this game that I have difficulty telling the difference between real life and a fantasy game. I just find it curious that so many people have so little respect for other people that they cannot honor so simple a request. If you want to inspect someone, ASK first. Its really not very difficult. And it goes the distance for good will. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 9:06:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Looking them up isn't built into the game. &nbsp;Prior knowledge of them isn't relevant. &nbsp;You don't have the stats listed.<br><br><i>If</i> Verant had the manpower and time (not to mention desire to add that much in the way of aesthetics) and <i>if</i> adding that many graphics on a global scale wasn't such a strain on throughput, there might've been some way for them to make every individual piece of equipment both visible and distinct. &nbsp;They can't do that, due to the lack of the mentioned criteria.<ul><li>To make up for the inability to just glance at a no-graphic Flowing Black Silk Sash and differentiate it from a no-graphic Spider Fur Belt (I'm pretty sure those items would look noticeably different), they added the inspect feature.<li>To make up for the inability to just glance at a fine steel short sword and differentiate it from a rusty short sword, they added the inspect feature.<li>To make up for the inability to see the difference between a plain copper ring and a platinum ring with a diamond in it (both of which would be too tiny to notice, given the size of the avatars and most people's monitors), they added the inspect feature.</ul>To see everything you can't see that you can see if you're right next to someone (no touching involved), they added the inspect feature. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uneebbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neebbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/10/02 9:06:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3400.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Inspections</span><hr size=1>   Being inspected is very mildly annoying to me. There are legitimate points that you cannot tell what people are wearing in EQ very well due to graphic limitations, but it is a bit rude to ignore the person playing the character and treat them like an NPC. Really, though, the major annoyance is the begging that may follow an inspection, not the inspection itself. If we talk about that then we'll be rehijaacking this thread.<br><br>  Oh, and people who auction in shout and ooc, even after being requested not to, are more annoying than being inspected. Fortunately, my ignore key works well, although I'm rarely any place that spams auctions galore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrechdashadowknight.showPublicProfile